\subsection{Structure of a Dirichlet group}
\begin{definition}\label{character.dirichlet.group.structure}
\uses{character.dirichlet.group,character.dirichlet.modulus}
The **structure** of a {{KNOWL('character.dirichlet.group', 'Dirichlet character group')}} of Dirichlet characters of {{KNOWL('character.dirichlet.modulus', 'modulus')}} $q$ refers to its isomorphism type as a finite abelian group, which can be uniquely expressed as a product of cyclic groups $C_{n_1}\times C_{n_2}\cdots\times C_{n_r}$ with $n_1|n_2|\cdots |n_r$.  This is the same as the structure of the group $(\Z/q\Z)^\times$.
\end{definition}


